    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Bush Prevails'' (front page, Dec. 13):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Bush Prevails'' (front page, Dec. 13):</p>
        <p>Although there will be a push to reform the voting process and to finance localities to improve voting machines, progress will be incremental and take a long time.</p>
        <p>One action can be taken immediately. Congress can mandate that elections for federal office take place over a minimum of two days, perhaps the first Monday and Tuesday of November. If there are problems or purported irregularities with voter access, ballots, personnel and so on, there would be time to correct them and allow people to vote properly on the second day.</p>
        <p>ALAN SCHOFFMAN  Teaneck, N.J., Dec. 13, 2000</p>
      </block>
